What you need to know:

On July 7, he said 2020 is a lost year due to the Covid-19 pandemic; that primary and secondary schools would not reopen until January 2021.By September 10, the message on reopening had changed to “we shall relook, depending on how the virus behaves”.By September 17, there was talk of a proposed November reopening, which Prof Magoha rebuffed but said many options were being explored because the infection curve was flattening , and “it is very good news for all of us”.